import random
def inside(p):
    x, y = random.random(), random.random()
    return x*x + y*y < 1

paragraphs.title: Read youtube dataset and converted into SPARK dataframe
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import *

file_path = "hdfs://nn/user/<user>/dataset/stg_youtube.csv"
youtube_schema=StructType([
    StructField("video_id", StringType(), True),
    StructField("trending_date", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("title", StringType(), True),
    StructField("channel_title", StringType(), True),
    StructField("category_id", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("publish_time", StringType(), True),
    StructField("tags", StringType(), True),
    StructField("views", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("likes", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("dislikes", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("comment_count", IntegerType(), True)
])


df_youtube = spark.read \
 .option("delimiter", "\t") \
 .schema(youtube_schema) \
 .option("inferSchema", "True") \
 .csv(file_path)

print ("Total Records: " + str( df_youtube.count()))
df_youtube.show(3, truncate=True)

%spark.pyspark
file_path = "hdfs://nn/user/<user>/dataset/video_category.dat"
youtube_vd_cat_schema=StructType([
    StructField("category_id", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("category_name", StringType(), True),
])


youtube_video_cat = spark.read \
 .option("delimiter", "|") \
 .schema(youtube_vd_cat_schema) \
 .option("inferSchema", "True") \
 .csv(file_path)

print ("Total Records: " + str( youtube_video_cat.count()))
youtube_video_cat.show(5, truncate=True)

paragraphs.title: SELECT trending_date, video_id, channel_title FROM youtube LIMIT 5
SELECT trending_date, count(1) num_video FROM youtube GROUP BY trending_date ORDER By trending_date DESC
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import col

df = df_youtube \
        .groupBy("trending_date") \
        .count() \
        .orderBy('trending_date', ascending=False) \
        .select(col("trending_date"), col("count").alias("num_video"))


df.show()

paragraphs.title: Most views category in dataframe
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql import functions as F

df_youtube \
        .groupBy("category_id") \
        .agg( \
            F.sum(col('views')).alias('total_views'), \
            F.avg(col('views')).alias('avg_views'), \
            F.count(F.lit(1)).alias('num_video') \
            ) \
        .orderBy('total_views', ascending=False) \
        .show()

%spark.pyspark
result = df_youtube_full \
        .groupBy("category_name") \
        .agg( \
            F.sum(col('views')).alias('total_views'), \
            F.avg(col('views')).alias('avg_views'), \
            F.count(F.lit(1)).alias('num_video') \
            ) \
        .orderBy('total_views', ascending=False) 
        
        
result.toPandas()

paragraphs.title: Most views category in dataframe
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
sqlContext.registerDataFrameAsTable(df_youtube_full, "youtube")
sqlContext.sql("""

SELECT category_name,
        sum(views) as total_views,
        avg(views) as avg_views,
        count(1) as num_video
FROM youtube
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY total_views DESC

""").show()

paragraphs.title: Most video category
paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import numpy as np


df2 = sqlContext.sql("SELECT category_name, count(1) as num_video \
                      FROM youtube \
                      GROUP BY category_name \
                      ORDER BY num_video DESC" \
                    )
result_pd_df = df2.toPandas()
sns.catplot(x='category_name', y='num_video', \
            data=result_pd_df, \
            order=result_pd_df['category_name'], \
            kind='bar')

%spark.pyspark

result_pd_df
## plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
ax = sns.barplot(y='category_name',x='num_video', \
                 data=result_pd_df, \
                 orient='h' \
                )
plt.xlabel("Number of Videos")
plt.ylabel("Categories")
plt.title("Catogories of trend videos")

%spark.pyspark
df2 = sqlContext.sql("""

SELECT video_id, count(1) as duration
FROM youtube
GROUP BY video_id
ORDER BY duration DESC"
                    
""")
result_pd_df = df2.toPandas()
result_pd_df.head(20)

%spark.pyspark
df2 = sqlContext.sql("SELECT category_name, sum(likes) as total_likes, \
                             sum(dislikes) as total_dislikes, \
                             (sum(likes)/sum(dislikes)) as ratio \
                      FROM youtube \
                      GROUP BY category_name \
                      ORDER BY ratio DESC" \
                    )
                    
result_pd_df = df2.toPandas()
result_pd_df.head(20)

%spark.pyspark

##plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
ax = sns.barplot(y='category_name',x='ratio', \
                 data=result_pd_df, \
                 orient='h' \
                )
plt.xlabel("Ratio")
plt.ylabel("Categories")
plt.title("Ratio like vs dislike video")
